The People of the State of Illinois, Respondent-Appellee, v. Benjamin Marshall, Petitioner-Appellant.(No. 58618;First District (2nd Division)February 26, 1974.

DOWNING, J., took no part.

James J. Doherty, Public Defender, of Chicago (Daniel Miranda, Assistant Public Defender, of counsel), for appellant.Bernard Carey, State’s Attorney, of Chicago (Kenneth L. Gillis and John M. Cutrone, Assistant State’s Attorneys, of counsel), for the People. PER CURIAM.
